28","1317":"1317","Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England":"Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England","Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":8,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":33,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":46,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":55,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William Hiltoft was born in 1282, in Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir William de Hiltoft Lord of Ingoldmells, was 22 and his mother, Agnes DeMunby, was 22. He married Alice de Muer about 1320, in England, United Kingdom. He died in 1366, in Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 84."},"et":{"1282–1366":"1282–1366","1292–1380":"1292–1380","1304–1350":"1304–1350","1313–1366":"1313–1366","1316–1375":"1316–1375","1260–1295":"1260–1295","1260–1335":"1260–1335","1295":"1295","Abt 1313":"umbes 1313","1350":"1350","1282":"1282","1260":"1260","abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1380":"1380","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1304":"1304","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1366":"1366","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England":"Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England","Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1282–1366":"1282–1366","1292–1380":"1292–1380","1304–1350":"1304–1350","1313–1366":"1313–1366","1316–1375":"1316–1375","1260–1295":"1260–1295","1260–1335":"1260–1335","1295":"1295","Abt 1313":"noin 1313","1350":"1350","1282":"1282","1260":"1260","abt 1320":"noin 1320","1380":"1380","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1304":"1304","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1366":"1366","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England":"Ingoldmells, Lincolnshire, England","Ingoldmells, Lincolns